<H3> <TI>   Shanghai To Set Up Market for `Outside' Laborers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1902072894 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 0401 GMT 
19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1902072894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, February 19 (CNS)--According to relevant 
municipal departments, Shanghai City is now busy making 
preparations for the establishment of markets for labour force 
coming from outside of the city. The move is considered helpful 
in introducing labourers into the city, the largest industrial 
base in the country, and beneficial to having this work done in 
an organized and ordered way and to the easing to a certain 
extent of the "labour wave" imposed upon the municipality. 
  The city has recently set up an office in charge of 
administration over such labourers employed by entities and 
units in the city. The markets designed for such labourers will 
be open to all places in the country and allow various places to 
export labourers to the city where the introduction of such 
workers will be subject to market competition. Those units 
needing such labourers, except in particular circumstances, will 
have to have approval from labour departments at the city's 
district or county level prior to recruiting such workers in 
designated markets of this kind, and a contract will be required 
to be signed between the employer and employee, becoming 
effective only after it is testified to and sealed by the market 
authorities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

