<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Planning To Build Second Subway </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2102131894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1306 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2102131894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, February 21 (XINHUA) -- Shanghai city will 
construct its second subway line, which is to run east-west 
under the Huangpu River. 
  The 27.3-kilometer subway will run from Hongqiao 
International Airport to the Pudong Railway Station. 
  According to China International Engineering Consulting 
Corporation, the No. 2 Subway will have 17 stops. 
  The No. 2 Subway will consist of two track tunnels, each 5.5 
meters in inner diameter. 
  It will intersect the No. 1 Subway at People's Park in the 
city center. 
  The first phase of the No. 2 Subway project, 13.38 
kilometers 
in length, will run from Jinganshi to Pudong district. 
  It is estimated that during rush hours, the subway will 
carry 
about 70,000 passengers per hour. 

</TEXT>

