<H3> <TI>   Shanghai To Build Centers for Returned Students </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1902070294 Beijing XINHUA in English 0649 GMT 19 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1902070294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, February 19 (XINHUA) -- The Shanghai 
Municipal Government has decided to build four special centers 
for returned Chinese students to apply what they have learned 
overseas. 
  The four centers will be located within the Zhangjiang 
High-Tech Industrial Zone in the Pudong New Area, the Xinxing 
Technological Development Zone at Caohejing, the Zone of 
Technological Development at Jiading and the Chedun Economic and 
Technological Development Zone in Songjiang County. 
  According to information from the Shanghai Municipal Service 
Center for returned Chinese students, about 100 returned 
students who have acquired doctor's or postgraduate's degrees in 
the United States, Japan and Canada have applied for starting 
their businesses in the Zhangjiang High-Tech Industrial Zone, 
where returned Chinese students can enjoy many preferential 
policies. 
  The Chedun Economic and Technological Development Zone, 
covering an area of 20 hectares, was set up recently by the 
shanghai University of Industry and Songjiang County. At 
present, construction of basic facilities has been completed in 
the zone. 
  Officials with the Chedun Economic and Technological 
Development Zone said they hoped to build the zone into a base 
for carrying out experimental application of newly-developed 
scientific and technological achievements and for industrial 
mass production. 
  The zone will offer a series of services to attract more 
returned Chinese students to launch businesses. The services 
include handling visas for the students, providing residential 
housing and workshops at perferential terms, offering legal 
consultancy, and helping find cooperation partners. 

</TEXT>

