<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Henan Wheat Production Situation `Grim' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1902050794 Zhengzhou Henan People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 1030 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK1902050794 </F>
<F P=104>  Zhengzhou Henan People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A provincial on-site meeting on spring wheat field 
management was held in Jiaozu City on 17 February. At present, 
the situation of wheat production in our province is grim. In 
more than 12 million mu of wheat fields across the province, the 
condition of wheat seedlings is generally poorer than that last 
year. The area of category-one seedlings has declined by 12.6 
percent over the same period last year, 10 million mu of wheat 
lack fertilizer, and the area of wheat hit by drought throughout 
the province has reached 40 million mu. If appropriate measures 
are not taken, a sharp decline in grain output will emerge in 
summer this year. 
  The meeting pointed out: Now is the crucial season for wheat 
field management, so various localities must seize this 
opportune moment, mobilize the masses, and rapidly set off an 
upsurge of wheat field management to bring about a change in the 
condition of wheat seedlings. The meeting also called for all 
localities to pay serious attention to major contradictions in 
light of the prominent problems that exist in various kinds of 
wheat fields. The fields that still need plowing, irrigating, 
and top-dressing should be done properly, the practice of rigid 
uniformity should be avoided, and efforts should concentrated on 
enhancing the efficiency of field management. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

