<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   MAC Rejects Cross-Strait Shipping Links Idea </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2002014494 Taipei Voice of Free China in English 0200 GMT 
19 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> OW2002014494 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei Voice of Free China </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "News" program] </F>
  [Text] The Mainland Affairs Council [MAC] on Thursday [17 
February] rejected the Economic Ministry's proposal to build 
direct shipping links across the Taiwan Strait. The Economic 
Ministry recently proposed that direct shipping links between 
specific ports in special zones in Taiwan and Mainland China be 
allowed, first to reduce transportation cost and time mainly for 
mainland-bound shipping from Taiwan and vice versa. But in a 
study report released Thursday, MAC said the cost of direct 
shipping links between specified ports or cities across the 
Strait is virtually the same as the cost of across-the-board 
direct shipping links between Taiwan and the mainland. The 
council argued that cross-Strait direct shipping links will be 
most likely accompanied by several major problems. These 
include Taiwan's greater reliance on Mainland China on the 
economic and trade front, a more rampant smuggling of Mainland 
Chinese products, and the illegal entry of mainlanders into 
Taiwan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

