<H3> <TI>   Kidnapped Experts in Yemen Set Free </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2102184894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1818 GMT 21 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2102184894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Sanaa, February 21 (XINHUA) -- The three Chinese 
experts, who were kidnapped while working on a road construction 
project, were set free today without any condition, thanks to 
the efforts of Yemeni security organs. 
  The experts belong to a technical team carrying out the 
project of building the Jahanna-Maareb highway in eastern Yemen. 
  The three Chinese, the head of the technical team, the chief 
engineer and the assistant manager of the project, who were 
kidnapped by gunmen on February 12, were in good health upon 
their release. 

</TEXT>

