<F P=100> East Europe </F>
<H3> <TI>   XINHUA Interviews Slovak Prime Minister on Upcoming Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1702050894 Beijing XINHUA in English 0205 GMT 17 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1702050894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bratislava, Slovak Republic, February 16 (XINHUA) 
-- The prime minister of the Slovak Republic, Vladimir Meciar, 
said today that he is looking forward to setting up closer 
economic ties with China during his forthcoming visit to the 
country. 
  In an interview with XINHUA, Meciar said Slovakia wishes to 
learn from China's experience in economic reforms and in 
establishing a market economy. 
  He said his country admires China's success in transferring 
a 
central-controlled economy into a market-oriented one. Learning 
how to achieve this transfer is very important for Slovakia, he 
added. 
  He also said that there are great potentials yet to be 
developed in economic relations between the two countries, and 
that he will bring new proposals to China. 
  He said that Chinese entrepreneurs will have opportunities 
to 
invest and get profits in a Slovakia which is undergoing an 
economic privatization process. He also wished that financial 
and monetary exchanges and cooperation with China will attain a 
higher level. 

</TEXT>

