<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   Local XINHUA Official Warns UK on `Un-Cooperative Stance' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1802161894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1603 GMT 18 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1802161894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, February 18 (XINHUA) -- A senior Chinese 
official here today warned the British side that its 
un-cooperative stance on the Hong Kong issue will by no means 
hold back the progress of the wheel of history. 
  Speaking at a public occasion tonight, NEW CHINA NEWS AGENCY 
[XINHUA] Hong Kong branch Director Zhou Nan said that the future 
of Hong Kong is after all in the hands of the great Chinese 
people including Hong Kong compatriots. 
  He reiterated that with the backing of the powerful 
motherland and the support of all the people in the country, we 
will surely overcome all the man-made obstacles on the course of 
progress to secure a smooth transition and guarantee long-term 
stability and prosperity in Hong Kong. 
  Zhou made the above remarks while reviewing the recent 
Sino-British relations in his speech. He said that we sincerely 
hoped that China and Britain could reach an agreement on the 
1994-95 electoral arrangements in Hong Kong on the basis of the 
"three conformities". 
  He said that the Chinese side had made its utmost efforts in 
order to reach an agreement with the British side. 
  However, the good will of the Chinese side and Hong Kong 
compatriots did not come true, he said, adding that the 
responsibility totally lies on the British side. 
  In his speech delivered at tonight's reception party held by 
the NEW CHINA NEWS AGENCY Hong Kong branch to celebrate the 
Lunar New Year, Zhou Nan also reviewed the recent development of 
the relations between Hong Kong and the Chinese mainland. 
  He said that the relationship between the two areas in the 
past year had become ever closer, adding that the booming 
economy of the Chinese mainland had enabled Hong Kong to retain 
its continued economic growth at a fairly high rate. 
  This, he said, had fully revealed that the stability and 
development in the Chinese mainland is the most solid foundation 
for prosperity and stability in Hong Kong. 
  He expressed his firm belief that the economic and trade 
relationship between Hong Kong and the Chinese mainland, 
together with exchanges and cooperation in the other fields, 
will enter a new stage in the coming new year. 
  Over a thousand people including local public figures from 
all walks of life in the territory such as leading businessmen 
Ann Tse-kai and Henry Fok Ying-tung, both of whom are also 
vice-chairman of the Chinese People's Political Consultative 
Conference, attended tonight's grand meeting. 

</TEXT>

