<H3> <TI>   Sino-British Joint Liaison Group Meets on Defense Issues </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2202140194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1341 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2202140194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hong Kong, February 22 (XINHUA) -- Experts of the 
two sides of Sino-British Joint Liaison Group held a meeting 
here today to discuss matters relating to Hong Kong's military 
sites and navy base. 
  Attending the meeting which is scheduled to last until 
Friday 
[25 February] are Luo Jiahuan, representative of the Chinese 
side, his British counterpart Alan Paul and their assistants. 
  Making comments to reporters prior to the meeting, Luo 
Jiahuan said that the Chinese side hopes that an agreement can 
be reached during the meeting. To achieve this, he said, the 
British side should show adequate flexibility. 
  During the meeting, participants will visit some local 
military sites. 

