<H3> <TI>   Cultural Exchange Plan Signed With Vietnam </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2202170894 Beijing XINHUA in English 1609 GMT 22 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2202170894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Hanoi, February 22 (XINHUA) -- China and Vietnam 
today signed an executive plan for improved cultural exchange 
between the two countries. 
  Under the plan, they will further strengthen their cultural 
cooperation and exchange in 1994. 
  About 30 groups including writers, artists, and those 
involved in the film, opera, photography and dancing sectors 
will exchange visits. 
  Meanwhile, film weeks and painting exhibitions will also be 
staged in the two countries. 
  The chief of the Bureau for Relations With Foreign Countries 
of the Chinese Culture Ministry, Wu Chunde, and the Vietnamese 
Culture and Information Vice Minister Vo Khac Lien signed the 
plan on behalf of their respective governments. 
  Wu Chunde, who was leading a government cultural delegation, 
arrived here on Monday for a week-long visit to Vietnam. 

